{
  "version": 1,
  "primitive": "sealed-poe-passphrase-negative",
  "source": "Passphrase-path negatives over the passphrase-n1 blob. A wrong passphrase, a tampered salt or params value, a flipped commitment header, an envelope spliced onto a different hashes claim, and a blob below the 48-byte structural floor all surface the single generic failure (TAMPERED_CIPHERTEXT) — the commitment cases fail BEFORE any STREAM chunk opens. Envelope-shape defects raise typed errors before any KDF work: an unregistered aead or passphrase alg, a nonce that is not 24 bytes, a salt outside 16..64 bytes, and Argon2id params below the registry floors. A whitespace-only passphrase normalizes to the empty string and is rejected with ENC_PASSPHRASE_EMPTY before any key derivation; a passphrase carrying a codepoint unassigned in Unicode 16.0 is rejected with ENC_PASSPHRASE_UNNORMALIZABLE before any normalization step runs. Typed caller-input rejections strictly precede the blob structural floor: a blob below 48 bytes paired with an unnormalizable passphrase still raises ENC_PASSPHRASE_UNNORMALIZABLE rather than failing generically.",
